title: 820-3332 Missing PM SLP S5
message:
This board is not liquid damaged

I have seen 4 3332 that show these same symptoms most liquid damage but this one isnt.  

PPBUS G3H is 12.4v
3v42 is 3.42
3.3v S5 is 3.3v
Computer will boot in SMC Bypass with no issue

Has no PM SLP S5 3.3v when charger is plugged in. Reballed SMC and checked pull down resistor for the SLP S5 line. All fine.

title: 820-3332 Missing PM SLP S5
message: Is the 15" dependent on the extra current available to boot or is it a signal line coming from the brick? It might just need a new cable end if its a signal issue

title: 820-3332 Missing PM SLP S5
message: The magsafe tip has a one-wire EEPROM in it. The system needs to see a valid charger before it will power on. So you just need an 85W charger and all macbook will power on from that.
